%N A396685 Numbers k such that 2*k is not the range of A002322, the reduced totient function.
%C A396685 Numbers k such that 2*k is not in A002174.
%C A396685 For prime p >= 5, p^k is in this sequence if and only if 2*p^k + 1 is composite: if psi(k) = 2*p^k, then k must have some prime power factor q such that psi(q) = 2*q^k. No prime power with exponent >= 2 can satisfy this equation, so q = 2*p^k + 1 must be prime. In particular, this sequence contains p^k with either p == 1 (mod 3) or k even (since then 2*p^k + 1 is divisible by 3).
%H A396685 Jianing Song, <a href="/A396685/b396685.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10001</a>
%o A396685 (PARI) isA396685(n) = !is(2*n) \\ See _Charles R Greathouse IV_'s second program in A002174
%Y A396685 Cf. A002322, A079695 (for EulerPhi), A396684 (complement).
